feat(R63): APTD implemented + 4-mode ablation -- decomposition validated (LPIPS win), SSIM not yet beating Bridge

aptd_model.py (WarpResidualHead modes direct/residual/warp/warpres + APTDNet reusing
SCDiT backbone, x0 endpoint param, zero-init -> starts at pre-op) + train_aptd.py
(span loss reduces to alpha-weighted endpoint + L_end + L_smooth(flow) + L_res(R); 1/4-NFE eval).

Ablation (val n=54, each from scratch 1200 steps, 1NFE):
  direct   SSIM 0.2097 LPIPS 0.4277
  residual SSIM 0.2044 LPIPS 0.4307
  warp     SSIM 0.2071 LPIPS 0.4939   (warp-only perceptually bad)
  warpres  SSIM 0.2208 LPIPS 0.4222   (FULL APTD: best on SSIM/PSNR/LPIPS)
Bridge ref (s2_base 5000 steps): SSIM 0.249 / LPIPS 0.509.

Findings: warpres best on all 3 internal metrics -> decomposition validated. R_new head is
critical (warp-only LPIPS 0.494 -> 0.422 with residual). Warp head contributes (warpres >
residual). Both components complementary. vs Bridge: APTD wins LPIPS big (0.422 vs 0.509)
but not SSIM/PSNR (0.221 vs 0.249) -- perceptual-distortion tradeoff amplified by identifiability.
Confounds: APTD only 1200 steps vs Bridge 5000; x0/1NFE vs velocity/4NFE; flow_scale=0.3 maybe large.

Next: train warpres to 5000 steps + tune flow_scale/lambda_smooth + bootstrap CIs to see if SSIM
catches up; else narrate via LPIPS/perceptual + honest tradeoff + PMOS secondary module.
